HEADWORD: Winger
<hw>Wing"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>One
of the casks stowed in the wings of a vessel's hold, being smaller than
such as are stowed more amidships.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
